CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 25, reads: "All Set For The Big Water Circus - This group of crack swimmers from the Mount Oliver Recreation Center will perform in Frogs' big "Water Circus" this Friday night, Aug. 9, at the Ammon Recreation Center pool. Recently they exhibited in the "Aquacade Ballet" at North Park and have given many exhibitions this summer.  Front row, left to right; Joan Bronder, Pat Mulvihill, Sally Weir, Joan Stilley, Back row: Jean Leuterbach, Audrey Schneider, Sally Kimmel, Patsy D[o]vers, C[eda] D[o]vers, Polly Kelly, Helen Lou Stilley and Jeannine Bronder. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women and girls, front row from left: Joan Bronder, Pat Mulvihill, Sally Weir, Joan Stilley; back row: Jean Leuterbach, Audrey Schneider, Sally Kimmel, Patsy Dovers, Ceda Dovers, Polly Kelly, Helen Lou Stilley and Jeannine Bronder, standing at swimming pool with frame house in background
